comments: Bridges (PHX) is moving slightly forward towards Fox (SAC) and marginal contact occurs with Fox's slightly extended left leg.
McGee (PHX) legally contests Jones' (SAC) shot near the rim.
Fox (SAC) is moving alongside Booker's (PHX) path and maintains a legal guarding position on the perimeter.
Crowder (PHX) is already in Mitchell's (SAC) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Metu (SAC) legally contests Paul's (PHX) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Paul (PHX) does not overtly or abnormally extend his leg into Metu (SAC) during his jump shot attempt.
Metu (SAC) applies a stayed hand to Paul's (PHX) side and marginal contact occurs as Paul is starting his upward shooting motion.
Metu (SAC) cleanly blocks Paul's (PHX) shot attempt while the ball is on its upward flight to the basket.

Replay review of the foul called on Booker (PHX) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful.  Barnes (SAC) initiates contact with Booker, who has established a legal guarding position in his path.
Mitchell (SAC) and Paul (PHX) come together at the same spot and make incidental foot to foot contact with one another in the backcourt.
McGee (PHX) is already in Fox's (SAC) path when contact occurs and he absorbs the contact.
Booker (PHX) is already in Mitchell's (SAC) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Paul (PHX) does not bring part of his hand under the ball when he brings his dribble to a pause.
Mitchell (SAC) releases away from Bridges (PHX) and marginal contact occurs as Mitchell secures the rebound.
Jones (SAC) is already in Booker's (PHX) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Booker (PHX) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Fox (SAC) that affects his shot near the rim.
Jones (SAC) extends his hand forward into Paul's (PHX) path and delivers contact that affects Paul's SQBR.
Fox (SAC) cleanly deflects the ball away from Paul (PHX).  Any ensuing arm contact after the deflection is considered incidental.
Fox (SAC) is bracing for the contact from Booker (PHX) and releases away from the contact.
Booker (PHX) releases away from Fox (SAC) and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Metu (SAC) commits a take foul on Booker (PHX).
Metu (SAC) and Booker (PHX) come together at the same spot and incidental contact occurs as they attempt to secure the loose ball.
